result.execSummary:
The defendant Warren G Hamilton-Hawthorne was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property >$10,000, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Warren G Hamilton-Hawthorne in court with attorney Michael S. Holzman.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
State has satisfied victim rights notification.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve  1 YEAR at the House of Corrections with 3 days credit CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence.  Defendant to serve 6 months straight time with general Huber for the remaining 6 months.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on 3 YEARS probation.  Probation can be terminated when restitution is paid in full.

  Conditions of Probation:
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any programs deemed necessary by the probation department.
- No possession/consumption/selling/distribution of illegal drugs/alcohol.
- Obtain/maintain fulltime employment/education/vocation.
- Provide a DNA sample.
- Follow all rules of supervision and follow through with any other treatment deemed necessary by the department.

Defendant Warren G Hamilton-Hawthorne in court with attorney Michael S. Holzman.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case in court for final pre-trial, however parties would like to proceed with a plea hearing instead.  Jury trial date of 06/10/2015 is vacated.
  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead NO CONTEST and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  Case is adjourned for sentencing in Branch 22.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for July 8, 2015 at 08:30 am.
